The paper deals with incorporating prior knowledge into neural sequence models for machine translation, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a moment matching framework, which involves optimizing the expectations of certain features, and this is a technique that is commonly used in machine learning and statistics, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with machine translation, which involves processing and generating text, and this is a task that is often tackled using computer vision techniques, falling under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
